  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently, the way a client updates its knowledge of peer's head root, head slot, finalized root, and finalized epoch is unspecified. The client only learns it on the handshake when requesting `STATUS` from a peer.\r\n\r\nWe could argue when the client is boosted, it only needs the information once and only needs to sync once. But in practice, some bad network conditions might require the client to resync again.\r\n\r\nWe should specify the client to request `STATUS` from peer once half an epoch to prevent the knowledge of peer too outdated and thus improve client stability.",
